ld everything.\n\n- Utsav\n|\nI stared at him (Dionysus). 'You're...you're married? But I thought you got in trouble for chasing a wood nymph-\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Titan's Curse\n|\nWith love that knew no fear, the Singer caught his torment, wrapped it all in song and gave it back to him as peace.\n\n- Calvin Miller, The Singer\n|\nStare up at the stars,Don't be fearful of the night.For, it is the darkness,That lets us know the light.\n\n- Kyra\n|\nWhere the mountain crosses.On top of the mountain, I do not myself know where.I wandered where my mind and my heart seemed to be lost.I wandered away.\n\n- Jane Bierhorst, In the Trail of the Wind: American Indian Poems and Ritual Orations\n|\nSometimes it’s best to stop searching for your passion. Instead, follow your curiosity and see where it leads.\n\n- Mensah Oteh, Unlocking Life's Treasure Chest: Wisdom keys to keep you inspired, encouraged, motivated and focused\n|\nA Maximus, the Gladiator lies in every human being. When the time comes, your Maximus within you will come out. It is not called destiny, it is an extended automatic self reflex\n\n- Anoop\n|\nForget about letting nature taking its course to make you wealthy, Cosmic Ordering works faster.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Cosmic Ordering Guide\n|\nIf crimes are committed they must be seen as a disease, and punishment as treatment rather than as social vengeance.\n\n- Daniel Guérin, Anarchism\n|\nAgainst the disease of writing one must take special precautions, since it is a dangerous and contagious disease.\n\n- Pierre Abélard, The Letters of Abélard and Héloïse\n|\nWhile spirituality provides an efficient and endless fuel for your mind and body, you must burn that fuel with human action towards your goals, dreams, and desires.\n\n- Steve Maraboli, Unapologetically You: Reflections on Life and the Human Experience\n|\nFor many, lack of achievement is more a consequence of fear of taking a chance and getting uncomfortable.\n\n- Steve Backley, The Champion in all 